ball.pre_text:
No slip in place. Over the wicket

1.59pm National anthems done. Keshav Maharaj has the new ball for South Africa despite a left-hand opener, Mohammad Naim, to go with Liton Das. Both the teams take the knee, including Quinton de Kock, who does so without a raised fist.

1.50pm Thanks Karthik, but I am not that ancient. I have been working since the 2007 World Cup, though, and already contemplating retirement. I have been to only three ICC events. And now I await two of my favourite anthems in cricket to go with Sri Lanka and West Indies.

John: "Definitely unlucky if a team goes out with just 1 loss, but how would that be different to say England making the final unbeaten then losing there? Also what's the point in a super 12 if 8 teams go through?"

Tom G: "With 6 teams in the group nowadays, maybe there is room for more teams in the knockouts? Maybe the 2nd and 3rd place teams play quarter finals with the group winners getting a bye to the semi finals?"

South Africa: 1 Reeza Hendricks, 2 Quinton de Kock (wk), 3 Rassie van der Dussen, 4 Temba Bavuma (capt), 5 Aiden Markram, 6 David Miller, 7 Dwaine Pretorius, 8 Kagiso Rabada, 9 Keshav Maharaj, 10 Anrich Nortje, 11 Tabraiz Shamsi

Bangladesh: 1 Mohammad Naim, 2 Liton Das (wk), 3 Shamim Hossain, 4 Soumya Sarkar, 5 Mushfiqur Rahim, 6 Mahmudullah (capt), 7 Afif Hossain, 8 Mahedi Hasan, 9 Nasum Ahmed, 10 Shoriful Islam, 11 Taskin Ahmed

1.40pm This is the first time Bangladesh are without Shakib Al Hasan in a T20 World Cup game, by the way. He's been involved in all their previous games since the 2007 edition. Sampath from our stats team says it's the first time he's missing a game in ICC limited-overs events since his debut in 2006. Wow.

On that note, here's someone who's probably been part of all those ICC tournaments as well, Sidharth Monga.

Calin: "I miss Tamim Iqbal's experience."

Abdul: "@Richard - definitely agree that this is a very unforgiving format, I would have liked to see a quarter-final stage to ease my nerves. As an SA fan, after that 1st loss to Aus, I was fearful of us making a swift exit. Must-win against Bangladesh and England, not feeling confident against the English team tbh"

Fahim: "Brave decision from Bangladesh to drop their best pacer in recent times. Fizz looks fatigued as well. As Bangladesh has little to no chance to qualify for Semis he should be rested before the Pakistan Series"

1.30pm South Africa have won the toss, and they'll bowl first. "This wicket looks a bit different to the others we've played on," Temba Bavuma says. "Looks like it will assist the quicks up front." South Africa are unchanged.

Two changes for Bangladesh. Shamim Hossain comes in for the injured Shakib, and Nasum Ahmed comes in for Mustafizur Rahman. Interesting that they've left him out and picked another left-arm spinner. Shamim bowls a bit of offspin too, but he's more of a batting allrounder.

"Of the three games we played, we were close to winning two," Mahmudullah says. "Having said that, it's time to play for our pride now."

Abdul Haseeb: "@dipanjan Shaw! Win the toss and bat first if and only if you have Jos Buttler in your team."

Richard: "This is an unforgiving format. Lose only 1 game and you could be out. It's going to be be harsh on 1 or 2 teams but it makes for an exciting tournament where every match and potentially every run counts. Sorry for Bangladesh but their tournament is done"

Sk Shahin : "Shakib ruled out means 2 player short in 11 "

1.15pm So what's gone wrong with Bangladesh's campaign? Is it the power-hitting, or lack thereof? Is it their catching? Or is it the case that they've been too anxious about results, and they've taken their eye off the process as a consequence? Take your pick.

In the USA, watch this match live on ESPN+ in English and in Hindi.

S: "Another Killer Miller special loading? Who remembers that hundred in 2017 and famous 19th over by Saifuddin."

Mark: "Bangladesh have nothing to lose here. They are all but mathematically out. South Africa have to win with a game against England coming. Plenty on this still."

Dipanjan Show: "England's performance yesterday should give the team losing toss some confidence."

saadat: "I have never seen such less interest going into a Bangladesh World Cup match, here in Dhaka."

Colin: "Would love to see Bangladesh cause an upset, but really can't see it. SA in the driving seat for the second semi spot however, they are South Africa!" -- They have England to face next as well.

1.05pm Afternoon, everyone. England are flying at the top of the Group 1 table and have one foot in the semi-finals, but below them there's a lot of jostling. South Africa are one of the teams doing the jostling, and they'd ideally want to win both their remaining games to ensure qualification. The first of those games is tonight, against a struggling Bangladesh team who are now without their talisman, with Shakib Al Hasan ruled out of the tournament with a hamstring injury. Abu Dhabi is the venue for this afternoon game, and we'll have he toss in just under half an hour. With me is Raghav, and we'll soon be joined by Sid Monga.
